President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Hawaii due to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration allows for Federal funding to be made available to State and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, for emergency protective measures. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has named Robert J. Fenton as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the State and deemed necessary. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.